[With the newly confirmed case and 2 newly reported fatalities, the total number of MERS-CoV infected individuals reported by South Korea is now 181 including 31 deaths, for a reported case fatality rate of 17.1 percent. The newly confirmed case is a 4th generation case, having been the physician caring for a 3rd generation case. The period of exposure is the latest period of exposure reported in this outbreak (11-15 Jun 2015), suggesting that breaks in infection control procedures are periodically occurring. We do not know if his contact patient (no. 135) is one of the patients that was in unstable condition and required intubation -- a procedure that carries a high risk of exposure to pulmonary viruses based on experiences with SARS-CoV (severe acute respiratory syndrome - coronavirus) back in 2002/2003.

The number of reported recoveries is now at 81 (representing 44.8 percent of cases), with 7 newly reported recoveries in the past 24 hours.

The HealthMap/ProMED map of South Korea can be found at https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=3465211,195. - Mod.MPP]

